Good.

18:43.155 --> 18:45.391
Guys, this is Johannes Betzler.

18:45.424 --> 18:46.759
The kid I told you about.

18:46.792 --> 18:48.627
Remember,
he stole a hand grenade

18:48.660 --> 18:50.463
and blew himself up
and as a result

18:50.496 --> 18:52.465
I got demoted for negligence.

18:52.498 --> 18:55.468
Now I get to work in this office
with all these wonderful kids.

18:56.135 --> 18:59.905
So, Jojo. I'm sure we can figure out
something for you to do.

18:59.938 --> 19:01.574
- Oh!
- Ideas?

19:01.607 --> 19:02.675
- Ja.
- Guys?

19:02.708 --> 19:04.076
Ja. Ja.

19:04.109 --> 19:07.913
Okay, well, we need somebody
to walk the clones.

19:09.748 --> 19:14.387
Also, I think maybe he could
hand out this new propaganda,

19:14.420 --> 19:17.724
and deliver these conscriptions.

19:18.056 --> 19:20.626
I don't suppose
I could be conscripted?

19:20.659 --> 19:21.694
Could I?

19:21.727 --> 19:23.095
Oh, yes,
that's a wonderful idea.

19:23.128 --> 19:24.697
Yes, I give my full permission

19:24.730 --> 19:26.766
for you to send this
ten-year-old child into war.

19:26.799 --> 19:28.166
Will someone get this kid a gun?

19:28.200 --> 19:30.011
And I'd be more than happy
to fight in the front.

19:30.035 --> 19:31.137
Get in line, kid.

19:31.170 --> 19:33.038
Okay. Here are
the conscriptions,

19:33.071 --> 19:34.140
and here is a gun.

19:34.173 --> 19:35.840
Ooh! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

19:35.874 --> 19:37.108
It's a bit... for the gun?

19:37.142 --> 19:38.411
No.

20:13.745 --> 20:14.781
Yuck.

20:17.015 --> 20:18.050
Look.

20:26.191 --> 20:27.460
What did they do?

20:29.194 --> 20:30.530
What they could.

20:31.830 --> 20:32.865
Come on.

20:48.947 --> 20:51.650
Hey-hey! Jojo Rabbit!

20:51.683 --> 20:54.552
Oh, look at your face.

20:54.586 --> 20:57.823
I am a soldier!
I'm going to war!

20:57.856 --> 20:59.758
And you are a postman!

21:01.093 --> 21:04.897
Jojo Rabbit, Jojo Rabbit!

21:05.664 --> 21:06.699
Mama?

21:08.033 --> 21:10.503
Field Marshal Jojo is home.

21:12.905 --> 21:13.940
Mama?

21:19.244 --> 21:22.748
Mama? I'm home.

21:24.883 --> 21:25.918
Mama?

21:43.835 --> 21:44.871
Mama?

23:55.834 --> 23:56.869
Hi.

24:37.175 --> 24:38.411
What do you want?

24:39.311 --> 24:40.680
Are you a ghost?

24:41.346 --> 24:43.715
Sure. A ghost.

24:52.057 --> 24:54.059
Don't make me run, kid.

24:54.092 --> 24:55.494
I'm far too hungry

24:55.527 --> 24:57.863
and you know how much
we love the taste of blood.

25:04.336 --> 25:05.404
Lose something?

25:07.072 --> 25:10.042
I'm not a ghost, Johannes.
I'm something worse,

25:10.075 --> 25:12.144
but I think you already
know that, don't you?

25:12.811 --> 25:13.846
You know what I am.

25:14.880 --> 25:16.815
- No.
- Yes.

25:16.848 --> 25:18.751
Say it.

25:18.784 --> 25:19.819
Say it!

25:20.352 --> 25:21.420
A Jew.

25:22.788 --> 25:23.856
Gesundheit.

25:24.856 --> 25:27.059
You can't be here.

25:27.092 --> 25:28.527
Well, your mother invited me,

25:28.560 --> 25:30.796
so I suppose that makes me
her guest.

25:30.829 --> 25:33.965
- It's not allowed.
- What will you do, sweet Hitlerchen?

25:33.999 --> 25:35.034
Hmm?

25:38.436 --> 25:39.472
Of course.

25:41.206 --> 25:42.408
Go on, then. Tell them.

25:44.342 --> 25:46.378
But do you know
what happens if you do?

25:47.345 --> 25:49.781
I'll tell them you helped me.

25:49.815 --> 25:51.817
And your mother, too.

25:51.850 --> 25:53.919
Then we'll all be kaputt.

25:53.952 --> 25:59.023
And if you tell her you know
about me, just one word...

26:00.192 --> 26:02.461
I'll do the world
a great, big favor

26:02.494 --> 26:04.329
and cut your Nazi head off.

26:05.831 --> 26:07.299
Got it?

26:07.332 --> 26:08.400
Ja.

26:17.475 --> 26:20.913
I think I'll hold onto this.
It's pretty.

26:28.920 --> 26:30.956
Sheesh. That was intense.

26:30.989 --> 26:33.425
- What am I going to do?
- Honestly, no idea.

26:33.458 --> 26:35.194
I mean,
there could be more of them.

26:35.227 --> 26:37.196
Hundreds of them
living in your walls.

26:39.631 --> 26:41.433
How did she get control
like that?

26:41.466 --> 26:42.935
She must've used her powers.

26:42.968 --> 26:44.002
Mind control.

26:44.035 --> 26:45.537
Oh, typical.

26:45.570 --> 26:48.005
- Did you see how fast she moved?
- Yes.

26:48.039 --> 26:50.474
Like a little,
female Jewish Jesse Owens.

26:50.508 --> 26:53.345
- And now she's got your fancy knife.
- My knife!

26:53.378 --> 26:56.181
Yeah. Like a little, female
Jewish Jesse Owens,

26:56.214 --> 26:58.050
Jack the Ripper.

26:58.083 --> 27:00.052
You're definitely
in a pickle, my friend.

27:00.085 --> 27:02.154
Ah, what to do, what to do?

27:02.187 --> 27:03.388
- Oh. Got it!
- Got it!

27:03.421 --> 27:04.932
- I will negotiate.
- Burn down the house

27:04.956 --> 27:06.925
and blame Winston Churchill.

27:06.958 --> 27:09.128
Or negotiate. Hmm.

27:24.609 --> 27:26.045
Excuse me?

27:27.412 --> 27:28.848
Little girl?

27:30.081 --> 27:33.152
Um... Jew girl in the wall?

27:34.953 --> 27:37.556
Yoo-hoo. Jew?

27:43.028 --> 27:48.433
Okay, well, I'll just say what
I have to say and that's this:

27:48.466 --> 27:52.638
I'm not scared of you and I think you
should find somewhere else to live.

27:52.671 --> 27:53.906
Okay?

27:55.006 --> 27:56.341
Not okay.

28:02.347 --> 28:04.282
Get the hell out of my room.

28:06.484 --> 28:08.520
She's pretty rude, you know?

28:08.553 --> 28:10.155
That's just my two Pfennige.

28:10.588 --> 28:12.691
- And now she's got two knives.
- I know!

28:12.724 --> 28:15.593
- How are you going to chop up stuff?
- I don't know!

28:15.627 --> 28:17.296
Oh, and she's
still up there, too.

28:17.329 --> 28:18.931
That... that thing, that, that...

28:18.964 --> 28:20.531
- Jew.
- Yeah. Jew, yeah.

28:20.565 --> 28:23.010
- What are we gonna do about that Jew?
- You think of something.

28:23.034 --> 28:24.970
Oh, now I'm the expert?

28:25.003 --> 28:27.506
Stop offering me
damned cigarettes! I'm ten!

28:27.539 --> 28:29.675
All right. Sorry.
I'm stressed out!

28:29.708 --> 28:32.210
Okay, let's talk like turkeys.

28:32.243 --> 28:35.179
You can't tell your mother
or that Jew will cut off your Nazi head,

28:35.213 --> 28:38.716
but there's no reason this thing
in the attic needs to ruin your life.

28:38.750 --> 28:41.619
In fact, you could use it
to your advantage.

28:41.653 --> 28:43.155
How?

28:43.188 --> 28:45.223
When someone tries to use
mind powers on me,

28:45.256 --> 28:46.258
know what I do?

28:46.291 --> 28:47.993
Use mind powers back on them.

28:48.026 --> 28:50.495
Remember last year when that
one-arm pirate von Stauffenberg

28:50.528 --> 28:52.130
tried to blow me up
with a table bomb?

28:52.163 --> 28:53.231
Yeah, you survived.

28:53.264 --> 28:54.299
Correctomundo.

28:54.332 --> 28:55.600
The only reason I survived,

28:55.633 --> 28:57.402
apart from having
bombproof legs,

28:57.435 --> 29:00.071
is because I outwitted
old von Stauffy.

29:00.105 --> 29:04.009
I let him think that I was dead,
when in actual fact, I was absolutely fine.

29:04.042 --> 29:07.279
By pretending I was dead,
I drew out all the traitors.

29:07.312 --> 29:08.514
So what are you going to do?

29:09.114 --> 29:10.148
Pretend I'm dead?

29:10.181 --> 29:12.551
Exactly. Wait, no.

29:12.584 --> 29:14.353
No, what I mean is this:

29:14.386 --> 29:16.355
make her feel safe
and then she'll drop her guard

29:16.388 --> 29:18.056
and then you will be
the one in control.

29:18.089 --> 29:21.025
- Reverse psychology.
- Don't complicate things.

29:21.059 --> 29:22.761
Just use my backwards
mind power trick,

29:22.794 --> 29:24.629
and everything will be fine.

29:24.662 --> 29:26.331
Ooh! I gotta go.

29:26.364 --> 29:28.404
We're having unicorn for dinner
at my place tonight.

29:28.733 --> 29:30.735
Concentrate, Jojo.

29:30.769 --> 29:33.005
Remember,
a Jew living in your wall

29:33.038 --> 29:35.339
is better than two Jews flying around
with their bat wings

29:35.373 --> 29:37.543
climbing down chimneys
and eating innocent Nazis.

29:38.543 --> 29:40.545
And don't give her
any more knives.

29:40.578 --> 29:41.613
Tschüss.

30:07.205 --> 30:10.275
Darling cub,
why are you up, huh?

30:10.308 --> 30:12.077
Did you eat anything, hmm?

30:12.110 --> 30:13.345
Sorry, I lost track of time.

30:13.378 --> 30:15.178
I was taking a long walk
and having a thing...

30:15.447 --> 30:18.283
What are we going to do
with these laces, huh? My goodness.

30:18.316 --> 30:20.285
You'll learn how to
tie them eventually, no?

30:20.318 --> 30:22.521
- I heard her.
- What?

30:22.554 --> 30:23.589
Who?

30:25.090 --> 30:26.158
Inge.

30:27.525 --> 30:29.161
Her ghost.

30:29.194 --> 30:32.031
Oh. That's so sad for you.

30:33.398 --> 30:34.533
You've lost your mind.

30:34.566 --> 30:35.834
It's sadder for me, though,

30:35.867 --> 30:37.603
because I have to live
with a crazy person.

30:40.505 --> 30:42.574
I heard noises. Upstairs.

30:42.607 --> 30:45.844
Ghosts? Honestly.
You know what I heard? Rats.

30:45.877 --> 30:47.846
Yes, we have them.
Can you believe that?

30:47.879 --> 30:49.614
Dirty animals.

30:49.647 --> 30:51.725
I've been meaning to tell you
to stay away from upstairs,

30:51.749 --> 30:53.485
until I've cleared
them all, okay?

30:53.518 --> 30:55.353
I don't need you getting sick.

30:55.386 --> 30:56.422
Okay, Mama.

30:57.489 --> 30:59.658
I'll watch out
for those dirty rats.

31:00.892 --> 31:03.062
Where are all
the goddamn knives?

31:17.575 --> 31:19.211
Are you going to bed, too?

31:20.478 --> 31:22.247
Yes. Soon.

31:22.280 --> 31:24.382
I have to tidy
some things first.

31:24.415 --> 31:25.451
What things?

31:27.152 --> 31:28.520
Mama things.

31:28.553 --> 31:29.663
Boy, you have to trust me, okay?

31:29.687 --> 31:31.390
I'm the boss here, ja?

31:32.657 --> 31:34.559
I guess.

31:34.592 --> 31:36.228
Good boy.

31:36.494 --> 31:38.831
Yes, but with... with one eye. Like...

31:40.365 --> 31:41.532
Almost.

31:42.300 --> 31:43.368
Not quite.

31:48.473 --> 31:50.608
Great. You got it.

31:50.642 --> 31:51.677
Ja.

31:57.482 --> 31:58.849
You have to be more quiet.

31:58.883 --> 32:00.452
He heard noises up here.

32:01.553 --> 32:04.123
If I have to choose
between you and my son, I...

32:09.260 --> 32:10.862
I won't know where to send you.

32:10.895 --> 32:12.597
You hear me?

32:12.630 --> 32:14.867
He can't know.
If he knows, then they know.

32:16.935 --> 32:19.436
- You could reason with him.
- You don't know him.

32:19.470 --> 32:21.140
He's a fanatic.

32:21.573 --> 32:23.250
It took him three weeks
to get over the fact

32:23.274 --> 32:24.843
that his grandfather
was not blond.

32:26.244 --> 32:27.746
I know he's in there somewhere.

32:28.846 --> 32:31.683
The little boy who loves to
play and runs to you

32:31.716 --> 32:33.552
because he's scared of thunder.

32:33.585 --> 32:35.654
Thinks you invented
chocolate cake.

32:38.489 --> 32:40.459
In the end, that's all you have.

32:41.626 --> 32:42.895
Hope...

32:44.096 --> 32:46.498
that your only remaining child
is not just another ghost.

32:47.932 --> 32:50.836
Perhaps we're all ghosts now.
We just don't know it.

32:52.370 --> 32:53.370
Perhaps.

32:55.406 --> 32:57.608
You've lived
more lifetimes than most.

32:59.510 --> 33:01.180
I haven't lived at all.

33:03.514 --> 33:04.883
You're being challenged.

33:05.950 --> 33:08.954
They say you can't live,
that you won't live.

33:08.987 --> 33:10.722
If that comes true,
then they win.

33:10.755 --> 33:12.191
They've been winning so far.

33:13.591 --> 33:15.894
They'll never win.
That's the power you have.

33:15.927 --> 33:19.731
As long as there's someone alive,
somewhere, then they lose.

33:19.764 --> 33:22.901
They didn't get you yesterday or today.
You make tomorrow the same.

33:26.437 --> 33:27.472
Hey.

33:28.706 --> 33:30.242
Tomorrow must be the same.

34:00.805 --> 34:02.440
Jesus Christ!

34:02.473 --> 34:03.808
You must stretch.

34:03.841 --> 34:05.019
Does that hurt you?

34:05.043 --> 34:07.646
- Yes.
- Good. Pain is your friend.

34:07.678 --> 34:09.513
Soon your leg will only be

34:09.547 --> 34:11.516
a little bit deformed
and pointless.

34:11.549 --> 34:13.952
I'm going to recommend another
month off school though

34:13.984 --> 34:16.588
because your face
might scare the other kids.

34:16.620 --> 34:18.422
It's kind of ugly.

34:18.455 --> 34:20.458
Okay, who's next?

34:25.062 --> 34:26.463
Jojo.

34:26.496 --> 34:27.799
Baby, I have to go.

34:30.801 --> 34:33.338
I'll see you at home. Mmm.

34:39.976 --> 34:41.913
- Hi, Captain K.
- Hey.

34:41.946 --> 34:43.357
If it isn't
Herr Hand Grenade himself.

34:43.380 --> 34:44.416
Ah.

34:44.447 --> 34:46.550
How's the leg, kid?

34:46.583 --> 34:48.351
It's pretty much healed.

34:48.386 --> 34:50.755
It only 80% hurts now.

34:50.788 --> 34:52.456
What are you guys doing?

34:52.489 --> 34:54.324
I'm being made
to teach the HJ boys

34:54.359 --> 34:56.094
water warfare training.

34:56.127 --> 34:57.862
You know, in case they ever need

34:57.895 --> 34:59.764
to go to battle
in a swimming pool.

35:03.368 --> 35:05.503
Can I ask you
a question about Jews?

35:05.536 --> 35:07.572
Oh, God. Why?

35:09.874 --> 35:11.709
What should I do if I see one?

35:11.743 --> 35:12.844
Ugh. Okay.

35:12.877 --> 35:15.613
If you see a Jew, you tell us,

35:15.646 --> 35:17.716
we tell the Gestapo,
and they tell the SS,

35:17.749 --> 35:19.451
and then they go
and they kill the Jew.

35:19.917 --> 35:21.520
And anyone who helped the Jew.

35:21.786 --> 35:24.356
And because these are very
paranoid times,

35:24.389 --> 35:26.358
probably some
other people just in case.

35:26.391 --> 35:27.858
It's a pretty drawn out process.

35:27.892 --> 35:31.496
Even if the Jew
hypnotized someone

35:31.529 --> 35:33.465
to make them hide
the Jew in the first place?

35:33.498 --> 35:34.999
I'd be amazed
if that could happen.

35:35.032 --> 35:36.601
No, it can happen.

35:41.873 --> 35:43.807
It happened to my uncle.

35:43.841 --> 35:45.510
A Jew hypnotized him

35:45.543 --> 35:48.512
and he became a massive
drunk and a gambler.

35:48.546 --> 35:50.115
And he cheated on his wife

35:50.148 --> 35:53.751
and he had an inappropriate
relationship with my sister.

35:53.785 --> 35:56.755
And then he drowned
in an unrelated accident,

35:56.788 --> 35:59.023
but it was the Jew's fault.

35:59.056 --> 36:01.593
Anyway. Did you see one?
A Jew.

36:02.994 --> 36:06.498
-I'm not sure I'd be able to tell if I did.
-Yeah, me neither.

36:06.531 --> 36:08.600
Without their funny hats,
it's damn near impossible.

36:08.900 --> 36:10.802
Someone should write a book
on the subject.

36:10.835 --> 36:12.479
It would make things so much easier.

36:12.503 --> 36:14.405
- It would be a hit.
- Ja.

36:16.140 --> 36:18.076
Finkie, they're drowning.
Come on.

36:19.577 --> 36:20.687
I'll see you later, little man.

36:40.198 --> 36:43.068
Okay, here's the situation.

36:44.035 --> 36:47.071
If I tell on you,
you'll be in big trouble,

36:47.104 --> 36:49.207
and I don't think you want that.

36:49.240 --> 36:52.110
But then you'll tell on me and my mother,
and we'll be in trouble,

36:52.143 --> 36:53.945
which I don't want.

36:53.978 --> 36:57.449
And if you tell my mother I know,
then she'll kick you out,

36:57.482 --> 36:59.117
which you don't want.

36:59.150 --> 37:01.885
And if I tell my mother I know,

37:01.919 --> 37:04.789
then you'll
cut off my Nazi head,

37:04.822 --> 37:06.724
which I also don't want.

37:08.226 --> 37:10.528
So, it's a Mexican stalemate.

37:10.561 --> 37:12.597
It's just a normal stalemate.

37:12.630 --> 37:14.965
I have some conditions
for allowing you to stay here.

37:14.999 --> 37:16.801
- "Conditions?"
- Yes.

37:16.834 --> 37:20.439
Tell me everything
about the Jewish race.

37:20.938 --> 37:21.972
Okay.

37:23.808 --> 37:24.943
We're like you,

37:26.677 --> 37:27.745
but human.

37:27.778 --> 37:29.948
Please take this seriously.

37:29.981 --> 37:32.217
Think of this as an exposé.

37:32.250 --> 37:34.085
I want to know all your secrets.

37:35.086 --> 37:37.589
Kindly refrain from sitting
on my sister's bed.

37:37.622 --> 37:39.824
Why? She doesn't need it.

37:39.857 --> 37:41.893
You know nothing of my sister.

37:41.926 --> 37:43.195
Inge and I were friends.

37:44.028 --> 37:45.730
I remember you.

37:45.763 --> 37:47.832
Such a funny little boy.

37:47.865 --> 37:49.901
Enough with the small talk.

37:49.934 --> 37:52.037
Start telling me
about your kind.

37:53.838 --> 37:56.207
Obviously, we are demons
who love money.

37:56.240 --> 37:57.542
Right?

37:57.575 --> 37:59.644
Obviously.
Everyone knows that.

37:59.677 --> 38:03.780
But what people don't know
is that we're also allergic to food.

38:03.814 --> 38:06.251
Cheese, bread, meat.

38:06.284 --> 38:07.986
That stuff
will kill us instantly.

38:08.019 --> 38:10.822
So, if you're thinking
of ending my life,

38:10.855 --> 38:12.690
that's the fastest way.

38:12.723 --> 38:14.493
Also biscuits, lethal.

38:16.994 --> 38:18.662
Very funny.

38:19.096 --> 38:21.099
Anyway, there's not enough
food for you,

38:21.132 --> 38:22.733
so I don't know
what you're going to do.

38:22.767 --> 38:25.670
Your mother managed
to find me some bread.

38:25.703 --> 38:28.940
She's kind.
She treats me like a person.

38:28.973 --> 38:31.075
But you're not.
Not a proper person.

38:31.108 --> 38:32.611
Are you?

38:34.712 --> 38:36.948
How dare you, Jew!

38:36.981 --> 38:40.618
You are weak like an eyelash.

38:40.651 --> 38:43.555
I am born of Aryan ancestry.

38:43.588 --> 38:47.124
My blood is the color
of a pure red rose.

38:47.158 --> 38:48.927
And my eyes are blue like...

38:50.294 --> 38:51.663
Break free.

38:52.330 --> 38:56.668
Break free, great Aryan.
There are no weak Jews.

38:57.201 --> 39:00.572
I am descended from those who
wrestle angels and kill giants.

39:00.605 --> 39:02.607
We were chosen by God.

39:03.274 --> 39:05.577
You were chosen by a
pathetic little man

39:05.610 --> 39:07.579
who can't even grow
a full mustache.

39:09.747 --> 39:10.949
The stronger race, huh?

39:19.056 --> 39:22.660
So, how's it all going
with that Jew thing upstairs?

39:22.693 --> 39:24.729
Well, she doesn't want
to talk to me.

39:24.762 --> 39:26.798
Mm-hmm. Well, you are a Nazi.

39:26.831 --> 39:28.599
I guess.

39:28.633 --> 39:31.069
This book is going
to be harder to write than I thought.

39:31.102 --> 39:32.938
Hmm.

39:35.973 --> 39:38.876
What's she doing? She's burning something.

39:38.909 --> 39:40.612
What is she burning?

39:40.645 --> 39:42.981
- What are you burning?
- She can't hear you.

39:43.014 --> 39:44.849
What are you burning?

39:56.293 --> 39:57.695
Why so happy?

39:57.728 --> 39:59.030
Things are changing.

39:59.063 --> 40:00.664
The Allies have taken Italy.

40:00.698 --> 40:02.934
France will be next
and soon the war will be over.

40:02.967 --> 40:06.003
Goddamn it!
Why does that make you happy?

40:06.037 --> 40:07.639
You hate your country that much?

40:07.672 --> 40:09.374
I love my country.
It's the war I hate.

40:09.407 --> 40:11.142
It's pointless and stupid,

40:11.175 --> 40:12.877
and the sooner
we have peace, the better.

40:12.910 --> 40:14.345
Oh, the war will end.

40:14.378 --> 40:17.048
We will crush our enemies
into dust.

40:17.081 --> 40:18.383
And when they are destroyed,

40:18.416 --> 40:20.051
we shall use
their graves as toilets.

40:20.084 --> 40:21.986
Okay. No more politics.

40:22.019 --> 40:24.287
Dinner is neutral ground.
This table is Switzerland.

40:24.321 --> 40:25.724
Let's eat.

40:34.832 --> 40:35.867
You aren't eating.

40:37.168 --> 40:39.871
No. I am not that hungry.

40:39.904 --> 40:41.673
I might eat later.

40:41.706 --> 40:44.075
For now, I am just going to
chew on these grapes.

40:47.712 --> 40:50.415
Well, I'm especially hungry
tonight.

40:50.448 --> 40:54.052
So maybe I'll just finish yours.

40:54.085 --> 40:55.654
Don't want it to go to waste.

41:10.468 --> 41:12.170
How was your day, Johannes?

41:12.203 --> 41:14.806
Oh, you know,
just wandered around,

41:14.839 --> 41:16.908
being a deformed kid
with nothing to live for.

41:16.941 --> 41:18.276
You're not deformed.

41:18.309 --> 41:22.080
My face looks like
a goddamn street map, woman.

41:23.314 --> 41:25.450
I wouldn't expect you
to understand.

41:25.483 --> 41:28.052
If my father were here,
he'd get it.

41:28.085 --> 41:29.887
Well, he's not.

41:29.920 --> 41:33.958
I know. And instead,
I'm stuck with you.

41:35.059 --> 41:36.194
You want your dad, 'eh?

41:36.227 --> 41:37.261
Yeah, I do.

41:37.294 --> 41:39.297
- Yeah? Yeah?
- Yeah. Yeah.

41:39.330 --> 41:40.465
- Yeah?
- Yeah!

41:40.498 --> 41:41.800
Fine.

41:54.145 --> 41:55.747
Don't you ever talk

41:55.780 --> 41:57.248
to your goddamn mother
like that!

42:14.365 --> 42:16.034
Paul, what happened?

42:17.468 --> 42:18.770
Paul?

42:18.803 --> 42:20.171
I yelled at the kid.

42:20.204 --> 42:22.407
What? Go apologize.

42:25.943 --> 42:26.978
Sorry, kid.

42:27.011 --> 42:28.279
What?

42:28.312 --> 42:29.981
What kind of apology was that?

42:39.290 --> 42:40.425
Sorry, kid.

42:44.595 --> 42:45.863
Jojo...

42:47.264 --> 42:49.901
I know you miss me, but I'm...

42:49.934 --> 42:52.970
I'm out there trying to make
a difference in the world.

42:53.337 --> 42:54.773
And while I'm gone,

42:55.539 --> 42:58.276
I need you
to take care of my Rosie.

42:59.844 --> 43:00.912
Can you do that?

43:03.547 --> 43:05.016
Yes, Dad.

43:05.516 --> 43:06.550
Thanks.

43:08.319 --> 43:09.554
She's doing what she can.

43:12.623 --> 43:15.293
Oh, gosh.
We made a good kid, huh?

43:16.427 --> 43:19.329
Mm-mm! Damn, that's good.

43:19.363 --> 43:23.100
It reminds me of dancing
with Rosie in The Red Salon.

43:23.133 --> 43:25.269
You remember, honey?

43:25.302 --> 43:26.838
Of course I do, babe.

43:35.346 --> 43:38.916
Hey, don't just sit there, kid.

43:38.949 --> 43:39.983
Come.

43:40.017 --> 43:41.452
Dance with your parents, come.

44:29.266 --> 44:33.137
So, I'd like you to draw
a picture of where Jews live.

44:33.170 --> 44:35.472
Where you all eat, sleep,

44:35.506 --> 44:37.575
and where the queen Jew
lays the eggs.

44:38.142 --> 44:39.543
You really are an idiot.

44:39.576 --> 44:41.256
Come on. We have a lot of work to do.

44:42.379 --> 44:43.681
Tell me about your family.

44:43.714 --> 44:45.316
I'll tell you about the Jews,

44:45.349 --> 44:47.093
but you are not privileged
to know about my family.

44:47.117 --> 44:48.586
But I need background.

44:48.619 --> 44:50.988
Why are you
hanging around with me?

44:51.021 --> 44:52.223
Don't you have any friends?

44:52.256 --> 44:53.925
Of course. Yorki.

44:53.958 --> 44:55.425
- "Yorki?"
- Amongst others.

44:55.459 --> 44:57.995
Well, you don't have anyone.

44:58.028 --> 44:59.230
I have Nathan.

44:59.263 --> 45:01.265
"Nathan?"
Who the hell is that?

45:01.298 --> 45:04.334
- My fiancé. I have him.
- Where is he?

45:04.368 --> 45:06.671
Fighting in the resistance, see.

45:09.073 --> 45:11.409
He proposed to me
on the banks of the Fluß.

45:11.442 --> 45:15.646
He knelt down like a proper gentleman,
recited a poem by Rilke.

45:15.679 --> 45:18.382
And when I said yes,
we danced into the night.

45:18.415 --> 45:20.251
Snore.

45:20.284 --> 45:21.385
Who's Rilke?

45:21.418 --> 45:23.387
A great poet.
Nathan's favorite.

45:23.420 --> 45:25.155
Oh, Nathan's favorite? Yay.

45:25.189 --> 45:27.959
He's coming to rescue me,
then we'll go live in Paris.

45:28.525 --> 45:30.595
You'd turn your back
on Germany forever?

45:31.295 --> 45:32.729
It turned on me first.

45:32.763 --> 45:34.632
Well, we don't need you.

45:34.665 --> 45:37.001
You and your stupid boyfriend
can shut up

45:37.034 --> 45:41.606
and go live in damn
cheese, snail, baguette land.

45:42.172 --> 45:44.375
Now, now, just because
you don't have a girlfriend.

45:44.408 --> 45:46.177
I'm way too busy for a girlfriend.

45:46.210 --> 45:48.412
One day, you'll make time.

45:48.445 --> 45:50.381
You'll think of nothing else.

45:51.148 --> 45:53.684
You'll meet someone
and spend your days

45:53.717 --> 45:56.954
dreaming of the moment you can
hold them in your arms again.

45:58.322 --> 45:59.356
That's love.

46:01.658 --> 46:03.561
- Ridiculous.
- Finished.

46:13.737 --> 46:16.340
I said to draw where Jews live.

46:16.373 --> 46:19.077
This is just a stupid picture
of my head.

46:19.476 --> 46:21.345
Yeah. That's where we live.

46:27.651 --> 46:30.454
Rilke, Rilke, Rilke.

46:30.487 --> 46:33.590
Where are you?
Poetry-writing dumbhead.

46:33.624 --> 46:34.692
Ah.

46:34.725 --> 46:37.294
Yes. Great thinking, Rabbit.

46:37.327 --> 46:40.363
We'll use all of these books to make
a fake floor that she'll fall through.

46:40.397 --> 46:42.733
Straight into
a pit full of piranhas

46:42.766 --> 46:45.670
and... and lava and bacon.

46:46.136 --> 46:47.714
- Why, she won't know what hit her.
- Shh!

46:47.738 --> 46:49.240
- Shh?
- Shh!

46:49.273 --> 46:51.041
You shush. Shush me?

46:51.075 --> 46:53.277
Let's get a book and let's go.
Libraries are dumb.

46:57.781 --> 47:01.685
Yeah, this is a really good idea,
what we're doing right now.

47:01.718 --> 47:05.390
If she had a heart, this would
break it clean in two.

47:08.158 --> 47:10.094
I have something to tell you.

47:10.127 --> 47:13.831
I came across
an old letter from Nathan,

47:13.864 --> 47:16.367
your fiancé, addressed to you.

47:16.400 --> 47:19.302
- What the hell are you talking about?
- I'll just read it.

47:21.138 --> 47:25.076
"Dear Elsa, this is hard
for me to say,

47:25.109 --> 47:27.645
"but I don't want
to marry you anymore.

47:28.712 --> 47:31.315
"I found a new woman
and we laugh a lot

47:31.348 --> 47:33.150
"and do the tongue-kiss.

47:33.183 --> 47:35.586
"It's like my favorite poet,
Rilke, says,

47:35.619 --> 47:40.658
"'We need in love to practice only this:
letting each other go.'

47:41.325 --> 47:44.095
"So, goodbye and sorry
about letting you go.

47:44.128 --> 47:47.731
"From Nathan, your ex-fiancé.

47:48.332 --> 47:51.202
"PS, I'm not really
in the resistance.

47:51.235 --> 47:52.369
"I was lying.

47:52.402 --> 47:55.073
I'm unemployed
and quite fat now."

48:20.731 --> 48:23.901
Um... don't open the door,

48:23.934 --> 48:28.406
but I actually forgot
there was a second letter.

48:28.872 --> 48:32.510
"Dear Elsa...

48:32.543 --> 48:37.280
"I just wanted to let you know that I don't
want to break up with you now.

48:37.314 --> 48:41.352
"I changed my mind because I don't want you
to kill yourself over me,

48:41.385 --> 48:43.687
"which a couple of girls
have done in the past,

48:43.720 --> 48:45.756
"and it's pretty stressful.

48:45.789 --> 48:47.691
"I need you to stay alive.

48:47.724 --> 48:50.260
"Thank God you're being
taken care of by that kid

48:50.294 --> 48:54.431
"who I must say is a remarkable young man
beyond his years.

48:54.464 --> 48:55.799
"And brave, too.

48:55.832 --> 48:57.868
"And let's still
get married sometime,

48:57.901 --> 48:59.803
"even though
I am truly unemployed

48:59.836 --> 49:01.539
"and have nothing
going on for me.

49:02.573 --> 49:05.710
Yours, Nathan."

49:14.418 --> 49:15.753
- Beethoven.
- Einstein.

49:15.786 --> 49:17.320
- Bach.
- Gershwin.

49:17.354 --> 49:19.323
Brahms. Wagner. Mozart.

49:19.356 --> 49:20.791
Musicians, is that all you have?

49:20.824 --> 49:21.858
Rilke.

49:21.892 --> 49:23.460
Oh, yeah, of course.

49:23.493 --> 49:25.663
Your favorite, Rilke.
Jewish mother.

49:25.696 --> 49:26.730
Dietrich, then.

49:26.763 --> 49:28.499
Houdini.

49:28.865 --> 49:31.969
- No. That's impossible.
- Believe it, brother.

49:32.002 --> 49:35.206
Just ask Pissarro, Modigliani,
Man Ray, Gertrude Stein,

49:35.239 --> 49:38.576
Mr. Moses and the king of them all,
Jesus Christi. Amen.

49:38.609 --> 49:39.877
Pew, pew, pew!

49:39.910 --> 49:41.679
Well, you're just saying
any old name now.

49:41.712 --> 49:44.582
I've never heard of these people
and now I'm fed up.

49:44.615 --> 49:45.950
Hey.

49:45.983 --> 49:47.618
If you find any more
of those letters,

49:47.651 --> 49:48.819
will you let me know?

49:49.286 --> 49:50.387
Sure.

49:50.420 --> 49:51.722
Okay.

49:51.755 --> 49:52.789
Bye.

49:55.692 --> 49:58.563
Ah, these banks used to be full of lovers.

49:59.529 --> 50:01.832
There was dancing and singing.

50:02.966 --> 50:05.002
Romance.

50:05.035 --> 50:07.304
There's no time for romance.

50:07.337 --> 50:08.572
We're at war.

50:08.605 --> 50:11.509
Oh. There's always time for romance.

50:12.009 --> 50:14.712
Someday you'll meet
someone special.

50:14.745 --> 50:16.847
Why does everyone
keep telling me that?

50:17.814 --> 50:19.417
Who else tells you that?

50:20.517 --> 50:22.319
Everyone.

50:22.352 --> 50:23.621
Anyway.

50:23.654 --> 50:24.922
It's a stupid idea.

50:24.955 --> 50:27.725
You're stupid.

50:27.758 --> 50:30.261
Love is the strongest thing
in the world.

50:30.294 --> 50:33.564
I think you'll find that metal
is the strongest thing in the world.

50:33.597 --> 50:36.400
Followed closely by dynamite,
and then muscles.

50:37.367 --> 50:40.504
Besides, I wouldn't
even know it if I saw it.

50:40.871 --> 50:42.606
Surprise, surprise.

50:42.639 --> 50:44.575
Your shoelaces are undone again.

50:46.743 --> 50:47.978
Oh, Jojo.

50:48.011 --> 50:49.914
You'll know when it happens.

50:50.981 --> 50:52.850
You'll feel it.

50:52.883 --> 50:53.985
It's a pain.

50:54.618 --> 50:56.587
- In my arse, I bet.
- In your tummy.

50:56.620 --> 50:59.257
Like, like, you're
full of butterflies.

50:59.990 --> 51:02.026
- Yuck.
- Yeah, "yuck."

51:03.327 --> 51:05.796
Come on, Shitler.
Let's get a move on.

51:06.997 --> 51:08.799
Whoa!

51:08.832 --> 51:10.701
- Hey!
- What's wrong with you?

51:10.734 --> 51:13.837
I'm worried about you, man.
Are you drunk? Again?

51:13.870 --> 51:15.306
Come on. Oh, God.

51:15.339 --> 51:17.041
Could you
please untie them?

51:17.074 --> 51:19.409
- You're really getting fat.
- I'm not...

51:19.443 --> 51:21.879
You know what? Why don't I
just leave you here, okay?

51:21.912 --> 51:23.681
- No.
- I'll come and get you tomorrow.

51:23.714 --> 51:25.449
- Okay? How about that?
- No. Mama, Mama!

51:25.482 --> 51:26.717
You'll figure it out, darling.

51:26.750 --> 51:28.385
- No!
- I'll meet you back at the house.

51:28.418 --> 51:30.621
- I'll see you tomorrow morning.
- Mama, Mama!

51:31.088 --> 51:32.990
You're growing up too fast.

51:33.023 --> 51:36.860
Ten-year-olds shouldn't be
celebrating war and talking politics.

51:36.893 --> 51:39.663
You should be climbing trees

51:39.696 --> 51:41.865
and then falling out of
those trees.

51:41.898 --> 51:43.800
But the Führer says when we win

51:43.834 --> 51:46.637
it is us, young boys
who will rule the world.

51:46.670 --> 51:47.704
Pfft!

51:48.905 --> 51:50.708
The Reich is dying.

51:50.741 --> 51:51.975
We're going to lose the war

51:52.008 --> 51:54.611
and then what are you
going to do, hmm?

51:54.644 --> 51:56.013
Life is a gift.

51:56.046 --> 51:58.582
We must celebrate it.

51:58.615 --> 52:02.886
We have to dance to show God
we are grateful to be alive.

52:09.159 --> 52:11.427
Well, I won't dance.

52:11.461 --> 52:13.630
Dancing is for people
who don't have a job.

52:13.663 --> 52:15.666
Dancing is for people
who are free.

52:15.699 --> 52:17.601
It's an escape from all this.

52:17.634 --> 52:20.471
Well, you're free
to dance your way home.

52:20.504 --> 52:21.972
I'll ride.

52:22.005 --> 52:23.106
Oh, no, you don't.

52:23.140 --> 52:24.775
No one can stop me.

52:44.127 --> 52:46.029
Welcome home, boys!

52:46.062 --> 52:47.965
Now, go home
and kiss your mothers!

53:08.185 --> 53:10.587
No news from Nathan today,
I'm afraid.

53:10.620 --> 53:12.689
He's probably doing
something amazing,

53:12.722 --> 53:14.892
like reading a book
or growing a beard.

53:18.662 --> 53:19.764
What's wrong?

53:22.732 --> 53:24.535
You want me to tell you
about the Jews?

53:25.202 --> 53:26.504
Don't care.

53:27.971 --> 53:30.741
In the beginning,
we used to live in caves.

53:31.208 --> 53:33.777
- Deep, deep in the center of the Earth.
- Wait.

53:33.810 --> 53:37.781
Scary places full of strange
and wonderful creatures

53:37.814 --> 53:39.450
all with one thing in common.

53:39.483 --> 53:41.685
Mm-hmm. Stealing
the ends of penises?

53:41.718 --> 53:43.654
No, you idiot.

53:43.687 --> 53:46.056
- The love of art.
- No cutting penises off?

53:46.089 --> 53:47.524
Do you want the story or not?

53:47.557 --> 53:49.860
You may continue,
but I know it's true.

53:49.893 --> 53:51.061
The penis thing.

53:51.094 --> 53:53.030
Rabbis use them for earplugs.

53:53.063 --> 53:54.831
And moving on.

53:54.865 --> 53:58.202
After many years of developing
magic and spells,

53:58.235 --> 54:02.238
we slowly moved out of
the caves and into the towns.

54:02.272 --> 54:05.843
Some of us stayed in the caves,
though, in animal bodies.

54:05.876 --> 54:08.679
Which are blobs or something?

54:08.712 --> 54:10.113
Well, I'll draw them for you.

54:23.693 --> 54:24.929
There.

54:25.762 --> 54:27.597
It'd be better with color.

54:27.898 --> 54:29.099
Where's the horns?

54:29.132 --> 54:30.166
Under the hair.

54:31.835 --> 54:33.136
Where's yours?

54:33.169 --> 54:34.738
I'm too young.

54:34.771 --> 54:37.641
- They grow when you turn 21.
- Oh.

54:37.674 --> 54:40.077
These days we live among normal people,

54:40.110 --> 54:42.278
but often we take over a house

54:42.312 --> 54:44.948
and hang from
the ceiling when we sleep.

54:44.981 --> 54:46.150
Like bats.

54:46.783 --> 54:48.852
Oh, and another thing is

54:48.885 --> 54:50.220
we can read each other's minds.

54:50.253 --> 54:52.155
Oh, my God.

54:52.188 --> 54:53.690
Everyone's minds?

54:53.723 --> 54:56.126
- What about German minds?
- No.

54:56.159 --> 54:58.729
Their heads are too thick
for us to penetrate.

54:59.696 --> 55:03.701
Like birds, our true language
sounds like singing.

55:05.001 --> 55:08.639
And we're also attracted
to shiny things.

55:08.972 --> 55:13.243
Crystals, glass and gold.

55:13.276 --> 55:17.114
"Attracted to shiny things."

55:18.315 --> 55:19.749
But also ugly things.

55:19.783 --> 55:21.552
Jews love ugliness.

55:21.585 --> 55:24.021
That's another thing
we learned at school.

55:24.054 --> 55:26.023
You love them, yes?

55:26.056 --> 55:27.091
Ugly things.

55:34.130 --> 55:35.332
Hi.

55:35.365 --> 55:37.267
You two seem to be
getting on well.

55:37.834 --> 55:39.970
I was just making sure
she was still alive.

55:40.003 --> 55:41.671
- What do you care?
- I don't.

55:41.705 --> 55:44.641
I just don't want
a dead person in my house.

55:44.674 --> 55:46.877
- How would you like it?
- I'd love it.

55:46.910 --> 55:48.845
More dead people
in my house, please.

55:48.878 --> 55:50.990
Look, just all the time
you two are spending together,

55:51.014 --> 55:53.083
it's making me feel
very uncomfortable.

55:53.116 --> 55:54.885
You suggested it
in the first place.

55:54.918 --> 55:55.986
Did I?

55:56.019 --> 55:57.654
- Yeah.
- Oh, yeah, I did.

55:57.687 --> 56:00.591
Besides, it's for the book.

56:01.257 --> 56:02.858
Oh, God, you're right.

56:02.892 --> 56:04.361
I'm sorry.
Did I make it weird?

56:04.394 --> 56:05.996
It's weird now, isn't it?

56:06.029 --> 56:08.098
It shouldn't be weird
between us.

56:08.131 --> 56:10.901
None of this should be weird.

56:10.934 --> 56:13.170
It's fine. I'm just tired.
I'm going to bed.

56:13.203 --> 56:15.138
Ja, I was just keeping
your bed warm for you.

56:15.171 --> 56:17.641
'Cause that's
what real friends do.

56:17.674 --> 56:19.710
Hey, what do think
about this uniform?

56:19.743 --> 56:21.320
I'm not sure
about the hips on the pants.

56:21.344 --> 56:22.780
Should they be bigger?

56:23.313 --> 56:25.682
- You look great.
- Thank you.

56:25.715 --> 56:28.952
Now, listen, Jojo.
Can I give you some really good advice?

56:29.252 --> 56:31.121
When you see what's in her mind

56:31.154 --> 56:33.857
and where she's trying
to make you go in your mind,

56:33.890 --> 56:37.160
in your mind,
you must go the other way.

56:37.193 --> 56:38.595
Get what I'm saying?

56:38.795 --> 56:40.896
Do not let her put you
in a brain prison.

56:40.930 --> 56:42.232
That, dear Jojo,

56:42.265 --> 56:45.769
is one thing that cannot
and must not ever,

56:45.802 --> 56:48.070
ever happen to a German!

56:48.104 --> 56:52.643
Do not let your German brain
be bossed around!

56:52.676 --> 56:56.179
I won't let her boss
my German brain around, mein Führer.

56:56.212 --> 56:57.648
Try not to.

56:59.049 --> 57:03.053
Now, I think you've got
a lot of good information in your book.

57:03.086 --> 57:05.389
It's time to show it
to the world, don't you think?

57:06.222 --> 57:07.257
Ja.

57:10.960 --> 57:12.696
- Adolf?
- Hmm?

57:12.729 --> 57:14.098
Do you think I'm ugly?

57:15.098 --> 57:16.200
Yes.

57:25.241 --> 57:26.877
Is he asleep?

57:26.910 --> 57:28.712
Mmm.

57:28.745 --> 57:29.847
He's different.

57:31.148 --> 57:33.916
He suspects something.
He thinks Inge's ghost lives up here.

57:37.987 --> 57:40.057
You remind me of her.
You really do.

57:41.491 --> 57:44.094
I would love to have seen her
